        "poet": "सर्वेश्वर दयाल सक्सेना / Sarveshwar Dayal Saxena",
        "poet_dates": "1927 - 1983",
        "poet_bio": "As one of the most celebrated figures of the modern hindi tradition, Sarveshwar Dayal Saxena explored themes of human suffering, beauty, and societal reform. Their poetry emerged from a close engagement with the historical and political movements of their time. By crafting verses that challenged established conventions, they revitalized the language and provided future generations of writers with a rich vocabulary of thought, introspection, and lyric intensity.",
