        "poet_dates": "1948 - 2020",
        "poet_bio": "As one of the most celebrated figures of the modern hindi tradition, Manglesh Dabral explored themes of human suffering, beauty, and societal reform. Their poetry emerged from a close engagement with the historical and political movements of their time. By crafting verses that challenged established conventions, they revitalized the language and provided future generations of writers with a rich vocabulary of thought, introspection, and lyric intensity.",
